President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate two individuals to key positions in his Administration. Patrick Hovakimian, currently the Associate Deputy Attorney General and Chief of Staff to Deputy Attorney General Jeffrey A. Rosen at the Department of Justice, is nominated to be General Counsel of the Office of the Director of National Intelligence. Hovakimian has experience as a Federal prosecutor, focusing on public corruption and white-collar crime. He also serves as a Commissioner of the Foreign Claims Settlement Commission of the United States.

Louis W. Bremer, currently a Managing Director at Cerberus Capital Management, is nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of Defense for Special Operations and Low Intensity Conflict. Bremer has spent the past 20 years focused on defense and national security investments. He previously served as a White House Fellow and was the Director of Strategy and Resources on the Homeland Security Council. Before his career in finance, Bremer served as a Naval Special Warfare (SEAL) officer for 8 years.